<p>However, the situation is far from ideal. Your wife will be giving birth in the next few weeks and she's deeply concerned about privacy during this critical and intimate time. The apartment feels crowded, and there's constant worry about the other family's children making too much noise.</p>

<p>You've had to lie to your landlord about the arrangement. Every day brings the fear of being discovered - not just risking eviction and legal trouble with the landlord, but also the terrifying possibility of deportation if authorities get involved.</p>

<p>You live in constant vigilance, coordinating schedules to avoid being seen together, keeping voices low, and living in fear. The cultural values of honor and honesty you were raised with clash painfully with the necessity of this deception.</p>
</div>

