<h3>Transportation Opportunity</h3>

<div class="consequence-text">
<p>A few days into the doubled-up living arrangement, the other family brings up an idea over dinner.</p>

<p>"We've been thinking," the husband says. "Both our families need reliable transportation to get to better-paying jobs. Rideshares and buses are eating up our income. What if we pooled our money and bought a car together?"</p>

<p>He's found a reliable used car for $1,600. If you split it, you'd each pay $800, plus about $75 each for insurance and $50 for registration fees. Total: $925 for each family.</p>

<p>"We'd need to coordinate schedules," he continues. "Share the car for work, errands, everything. It won't always be convenient, but it would save us both money in the long run and open up job opportunities further from the bus routes."</p>

<p>You have $<<= $money>> in savings. The car-sharing would cost $925 upfront.</p>
</div>

<hr>

<h4>What do you want to do?</h4>

<div class="housing-choice">
<<if $money >= 925>>
    <<link "Share the car with them ($925)">>
        <<set $money -= 925>>
        <<set $hasCar = true>>
        <<set $carOwnership = "shared">>
        <<set $familyHealth += 10>> /* Building trust through shared investment */
        <<set $familyHealth = Math.min(100, $familyHealth)>>
        <<goto "UnaffordableCarShared">>
    <</link>>
    <p><em>Split the cost and share the car. This builds trust and cooperation with the family you're living with.</em></p>
<<else>>
    <p style="color: gray;"><em>Share the car ($925) - You don't have enough money</em></p>
<</if>>
</div>

<hr>

<div class="housing-choice">
<<link "Decline the offer">>
