<p>But the apartment was already too small for two families. With an additional person, it's unbearable. The bathroom schedule becomes a nightmare. Kitchen space is impossible to share. Noise from the crying baby at all hours wears everyone down.</p>

<p>Worse, household responsibilities aren't shared evenly. Your wife's friend, focused entirely on helping with the baby, doesn't contribute to cleaning or cooking for everyone. The other family starts to feel like they're being taken advantage of.</p>

<p>After two weeks, the other family has had enough.</p>

<p>"We're leaving," they tell you. "We found another place. We can't live like this anymore."</p>

<<if $carOwnership === "shared">>
